{"word":"ἁπαλός","slug":"ἁπαλός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἁπαλός, ή, όν</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ orig.\">orig.</a> uncertain, but <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ὀπός</el> ‘sap’; ‘soft to the touch’] of growing things that are not hard or tough, such as young shoots of a fig-tree <b><i>tender</i> <a href='B:470 24:32'>Mt 24:32</a>; <a href='B:480 13:28'>Mk 13:28</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπαλλοτριόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπαντάω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}